Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Tunisian Spice Blend{1%tbsp}, half the @yogurt{2%tbsp}, half the garlic (you'll use the rest of the yogurt and garlic later), @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP olive oil and 2 tsp salt.)

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with paper towels. Add to bowl with marinade
and turn to coat. Set aside until ready to use in Step 4.

== Chili-Roasted Carrots ==

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%oz} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.
Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and
@chili flakes{1%tsp}.

Roast on top rack until golden brown and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Garlic Sauce ==

While carrots roast, in a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, remaining yogurt, and remaining garlic to taste. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{}, preferably nonstick, over medium
heat.

Remove chicken from marinade; allow excess to drip off. Add to pan and cook
until browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes} per side.

> TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Once cool enough to
handle, slice crosswise.

== Lemony Couscous ==

Meanwhile, melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over
medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%oz} and a pinch of salt; cook,
stirring, until toasted, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4).
Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until couscous is
tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in lemon zest to taste. Season with salt and
pepper.

Divide chicken, couscous, and carrots between plates. Top chicken with garlic
sauce and cilantro; sprinkle with remaining chili flakes if desired. Serve with
remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.